      "body": "Yes, it is a bit fuzzy, but printing the flags to the CI log doesn't solve the problems listed in the motivation either, because to confirm that a flag is used for *all* compilations in a successful compilation, one will have to go through *all* lines. Without a script, I don't see anyone doing that manually. In fact, this change makes the log so bloated that the scrollback will normally truncate it, so it is more likely that the change is going to hide issues instead of surface them.\r\n\r\n",
